ontrol over URLs through aliasing, which is often used to make URLs more readable or easy to remember. For example, the alias \'about\' may be mapped onto the post at the system path \'node/1\', creating a more meaningful URL. Each system path can have multiple aliases.','none'),(2880,'','default','Enter the path you wish to create the alias for, followed by the name of the new alias.','none'),(2881,'','default','The alias has been deleted.','none'),(2882,'','default','The path is already in use.','none'),(2883,'','default','URL aliases','none'),(2884,'','default','Change your site\'s URL paths by aliasing them.','none'),(2885,'','default','Edit alias','none'),(2886,'','default','Delete alias','none'),(2887,'','default','Add alias','none'),(2888,'','default','Allows users to rename URLs.','6.26'),(2889,'','default','The PHP filter adds the ability to include PHP code in posts. PHP is a general-purpose scripting language widely-used for web development; the content management system used by this website has been developed using PHP.','none'),(2890,'','default','Through the PHP filter, users with the proper permission may include custom PHP code within a page of the site. While this is a powerful and flexible feature if used by a trusted user with PHP experience, it is a significant and dangerous security risk in the hands of a malicious user. Even a trusted user may accidentally compromise the site by entering malformed or incorrect PHP code. Only the most trusted users should be granted permission to use the PHP filter, and all PHP code added through the PHP filter should be carefully examined before use.','none'),(2891,'','default','<a href=\"@drupal\">Drupal.org</a> offers <a href=\"@php-snippets\">some example PHP snippets</a>, or you can create your own with some PHP experience and knowledge of the Drupal system.','none'),(2892,'','default','For more information, see the online handbook entry for <a href=\"@php\">PHP module</a>.','none'),(2893,'','default','You 